SYNTAX:


LOGIC:
1) Can't have two same scope variables of same name
2) can't assign one type variable with a literal value of a another (String a = 1;)
3) A final variable can't receive a second value.
4) if an undecalred (in that line) variable is assigned a new value, it must have been previously declared.
5) If variable a is assigned with the value of variable b, b must be of the same type as a.
6) A local variable can't be referenced BEFORE it has been initialized or declared, but a global variable CAN
as long as that that reference comes inside method.  
7) If a global variable is not initialized globally, any method that references it must first 
intialize it.  

  
